critique: This document pertains to tax returns being open to inspection by a Senate Committee. It is difficult to assess its position on the traditional left-right political spectrum. There's no direct impact on immigration. The order itself doesn't expand executive power significantly, as it's enabling a Senate Committee's work. It doesn't obviously shift power between state and federal levels. It's primarily about oversight, so it's hard to place on the security vs. liberty axis. It's related to tax, but doesn't obviously increase or decrease regulation. It doesn't directly address social inclusion.
